Adding colors to your LaTeX file
By default the export is black and white.You can add color to your latex element by using the following command: {\color{&lt;color name&gt;}&lt;element text&gt;}
You can color entire sections using the following global definitions: 
\usepackage{sectsty}
\chapterfont{\color{brown}}
\sectionfont{\color{brown}}
\subsectionfont{\color{brown}}
\subsubsectionfont{\color{teal}}
\date{\color{brown}June 10, 2019}
You can deep dive into LaTeX if you want to customize it completely.  This brings us to the end of this post. Hope you will find it useful!
